{"lemma":"دَمْعُ","slug":"دَمْعُ","root":"د.م.ع","root_slug":"د-م-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/د-م-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"دَمْع","root":"دمع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13090","n13091","n13092"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tears","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"وَإِذَا سَمِعُوا مَا أُنْزِلَ إِلَى ٱلرَّسُولِ تَرَىٰ أَعْيُنَهُمْ تَفِيضُ مِنَ ٱلدَّمْعِ مِمَّا عَرَفُوا مِنَ ٱلْحَقِّ"},{"text":"قَبَّلْتُهَا وَدُمُوعِي مَزْجُ أَدْمُعِهَا // وَقَبَّلَتْنِي عَلَى خَوْفٍ فَمًا لِفَمِ\nفَذُقْتُ مَاءَ حَيَاةٍ مِنْ مُقَبَّلِهَا // لَوْ صَابَ تُرْبًا لَأَحْيَا سَالِفَ الْأُمَمِ","english":"I kissed her, and my tears mixed with hers, // and she kissed me timidly, mouth to mouth.\nI tasted the water of life from her kiss, // which may revive the ancestors, if it hit the earth."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to tear (to produce tears)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root د م ع (d m ʕ). Compare Hebrew דִּמְעָה (dim'á, dimʿā) and Ugaritic 𐎄𐎎𐎓 (dmʿ)."},"ipa":["/damʕ/","/da.ma.ʕa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13090","headword_ar":"دَمْعٌ","root":"dmE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tears;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fluid, of the eye;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether from grief or joy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) originally an inf. n.: (Msb:) [but having a pl., both of mult. and of pauc.: for] the pl. [of mult.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dumuwEN","text_ar":"دُمُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adomuEN","text_ar":"اَدْمُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damoEpN","text_ar":"دَمْعةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is the n. un., signifying]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single drop thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tear:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K:) if from joy, it is cool; or if from grief, hot. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damoEu daAwuwda","text_ar":"دَمْعُ دَاوُودَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"David's tears;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain well known medicine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K:) [perhaps"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fruits of a species of coix,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coix lachryma, now called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damoEu A^ay~uwba","text_ar":"دَمْعُ اَيُّوبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Job's tears, which are hard and stony, and are said to be strengthening and diuretic."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakati","text_ar":"بَكَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amaA'u wadamoEu Als~aHaAbi saAli","text_ar":"السَّمَاءُ وَدَمْعُ السَّحَابِ سَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sky wept, and the tears of the clouds flowed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aribi damoEapN","text_ar":"شَرِبِ دَمْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkaromi","text_ar":"الكَرْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He drank the tear of the vine"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wine."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dumuwEi Aljafonapi","text_ar":"دُمُوعِ الجَفْنَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tears,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the grease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gravy, of the bowl."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Msb","TA","S","Sgh"]},{"entry_id":"n13091","headword_ar":"دَمِعٌ","root":"dmE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"text","text":"masc. of]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damiEapN","text_ar":"دَمِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick to shed tears:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick to weep, abounding with tears;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damiyEN","text_ar":"دَمِيعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lh, L;) of which latter, which is applied also to a man, the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dumaEaA='u","text_ar":"دُمَعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to men, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damoEaY","text_ar":"دَمْعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to men and to women, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damaAy^iEu","text_ar":"دَمَايِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to women. (L.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damuwEN","text_ar":"دَمُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n13092","headword_ar":"دُمُعٌ","root":"dmE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mark made with a hot iron in the part where the tears run,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Ahmar, S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a camel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Ahmar;) said by Aboo-'Alee, in the “Tedhkireh,” to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small line."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}